{"_id":"1ylTW1N4aeI2CWdp","name":"Echopraxic Imago","type":"mech_system","img":"systems/lancer/assets/icons/mech_system.svg","data":{"cascading":false,"counters":[],"deployables":[],"destroyed":false,"effect":"<p>This electronic warfare system can only be used to perform the <strong>Echopraxic Imago</strong> tactic:</p>","lid":"ms_P5EQVCuUgBSvTPdlS3aKo","integrated":[],"license":"","license_level":1,"name":"Echopraxic Imago","source":null,"tags":[{"val":1,"tag":{"id":"060yGC97tWUriLGk","fallback_lid":"tg_unique","type":"tag","reg_name":"comp_core"}},{"val":1,"tag":{"id":"JwqNMHKcDL3Cxz3G","fallback_lid":"tg_ena4nNzrrSQIF4jvacv6L","type":"tag","reg_name":"game"}},{"val":1,"tag":{"id":"y26LL8HRL2XMZuxM","fallback_lid":"tg_78SWgJLYkLyBOoZqDfDxY","type":"tag","reg_name":"game"}},{"val":"10","tag":{"id":"hQUWmHtgOaF05Wfk","fallback_lid":"tg_JQGuxAyQxFGpfJRQFvwoQ","type":"tag","reg_name":"game"}}],"sp":1,"uses":0,"actions":[{"lid":"act_UthyUblczxfFxAV5Sb2_9","name":"Echopraxic Imago (Tactic)","activation":"Quick","terse":"Terse Description","detail":"<p>You introduce a viral logic bomb into the systems of a hostile <strong>CAPITAL SHIP</strong>, which is treated as a boarding action. This bomb takes hold during the <strong>Boarding Phase</strong>, attempting one of the following commands (your choice):<br /><br />&bull; <strong>Induce Nostalgic Loop:</strong> Until the end of its next turn, the boarded ship&rsquo;s battlegroup rolls twice for <strong>Interdiction</strong> and takes the worse result. While this effect is active, if any of the affected battlegroup&rsquo;s final<strong> Interdiction</strong> rolls result in a 1 on any die, the affected ship takes <strong>3 damage</strong>.<br /><br />&bull; <strong>Inflict Ontological Parasite:</strong> Choose a range band. Until the end of its next turn, the boarded battlegroup&rsquo;s attack rolls against targets in that range band have a 50 percent chance to miss outright before the attack is made. Roll a die or flip a coin to determine if the attack misses. This does not stack with <strong>Defensive Screen</strong>; the defender chooses which effect to apply. Additionally, the boarded battlegroup cannot choose that range band for abilities that affect or target specific ranges.</p>","cost":1,"frequency":"","init":"","trigger":"","pilot":true,"mech":true,"heat_cost":0,"synergy_locations":[],"damage":[],"range":[],"confirm":["CONFIRM"],"hide_active":false,"ignore_used":false,"log":""}],"bonuses":[],"synergies":[],"description":"<p>Conventional systemic attacks are largely ineffective at the scale of most fleet legions. To engage enemy legionspace gestalts requires more powerful &ndash; and more esoteric &ndash; methods of electronic/ontologic warfare.</p>","type":"System"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"HHrm6UaHtCrg3Wzn":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"4NdXiB56bKoSfDmF","name":"Cleared to Land","type":"mech_system","img":"systems/lancer/assets/icons/mech_system.svg","data":{"cascading":false,"counters":[],"deployables":[],"destroyed":false,"effect":"<p>Gain the <strong>Cleared to Land</strong> tactic.</p>","lid":"ms_TbibF8A7ThTNlIb2CG8dU","integrated":[],"license":"","license_level":0,"name":"Cleared to Land","source":null,"tags":[{"val":1,"tag":{"id":"GsPrdH4DG2a0xrTW","fallback_lid":"tg_limited","type":"tag","reg_name":"comp_core"}},{"val":1,"tag":{"id":"060yGC97tWUriLGk","fallback_lid":"tg_unique","type":"tag","reg_name":"comp_core"}}],"sp":1,"uses":0,"actions":[{"lid":"act_iZQFubA_u7_RHxdjkl6zF","name":"Cleared to Land (Tactic)","activation":"Quick","terse":"<p>All of your ESCORTS and WINGS or all ESCORTS and WINGS belonging to an allied battlegroup in the same range band as you repair 2 HP. One ESCORT or WING of your choice in that battlegroup may repair 4 HP instead.</p>","detail":"<p>All of your ESCORTS and WINGS or all ESCORTS and WINGS belonging to an allied battlegroup in the same range band as you repair 2 HP. One ESCORT or WING of your choice in that battlegroup may repair 4 HP instead.</p>","cost":1,"frequency":"","init":"","trigger":"","pilot":true,"mech":true,"heat_cost":0,"synergy_locations":[],"damage":[],"range":[],"confirm":["CONFIRM"],"hide_active":false,"ignore_used":false,"log":""}],"bonuses":[],"synergies":[],"description":"<p>A deckie has one job: keep the deck clear, planes loaded, bombers crewed, marines in their pens, subalterns packed, wounded cleared, fires suppressed, munitions clean&hellip;</p>","type":"System"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"HHrm6UaHtCrg3Wzn":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"AwYahEzM1516s4Uw","name":"Subaltern Combat Crews","type":"mech_system","img":"systems/lancer/assets/icons/mech_system.svg","data":{"cascading":false,"counters":[{"lid":"tempLID","name":"Reloading","val":0,"max":3,"min":0}],"deployables":[],"destroyed":false,"effect":"<p>You may use an additional <strong>Tactic</strong> during your turn</p>","lid":"ms_dvkRwENwuLp07R-8GD8jZ","integrated":[],"license":"","license_level":2,"name":"Subaltern Combat Crews","source":null,"tags":[{"val":1,"tag":{"id":"060yGC97tWUriLGk","fallback_lid":"tg_unique","type":"tag","reg_name":"comp_core"}},{"val":"3","tag":{"id":"4zljqurutuldbJiO","fallback_lid":"tg_8FBdSdkbLqsDsDmyJwlCa","type":"tag","reg_name":"game"}}],"sp":1,"uses":0,"actions":[],"bonuses":[],"synergies":[],"description":"<p>A certain percentage of most naval crews are comprised of subalterns by default, their resilient nature, immunity to hazards like decompression and hard vacuum, and NHP platform-compatibility making them valuable additions to any vessel. A much more significant portion of your fleet&rsquo;s crew consists of subalterns, however, increasing the speed and efficiency of all combat operations. Such crews have a noted tendency to be more vulnerable to command chain disruption and systemic attacks, drawbacks that keep the practice from being more widely standardized.</p>","type":"System"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"HHrm6UaHtCrg3Wzn":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"B1JFpRf2cfFAWCKj","name":"Smartscreen","type":"mech_system","img":"systems/lancer/assets/icons/mech_system.svg","data":{"cascading":false,"counters":[],"deployables":[],"destroyed":false,"effect":"<p>This ship is orbited by a screen of baffler drones. The first single-target attack made against it each round receives <strong>+1 DIFFICULTY</strong>.</p>","lid":"ms_xUvidvIBBeFU6DhwOXBCR","integrated":[],"license":"","license_level":1,"name":"Smartscreen","source":null,"tags":[],"sp":1,"uses":0,"actions":[],"bonuses":[],"synergies":[],"description":"<p>Smartscreens use physical-presence spoof and baffle drones to interrupt enemy smart and guided weapons along with hostile targeting systems, layering additional defensive measures to ensure vessel survival. Repeated assaults are capable of overwhelming the screen&rsquo;s defensive countermeasures, forcing commanders to remain mindful of the system&rsquo;s limitations.</p>","type":"System"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"HHrm6UaHtCrg3Wzn":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"Fg94Ez0j8T2iUmfe","name":"Power Distribution Systems","type":"mech_system","img":"systems/lancer/assets/icons/mech_system.svg","data":{"cascading":false,"counters":[{"lid":"tempLID","name":"Divert to Defense Reload","val":0,"max":2,"min":0},{"lid":"tempLID","name":"Divert to Weapons Limited","val":1,"max":1,"min":0}],"deployables":[],"destroyed":false,"effect":"<p>Gain the <strong>Divert Power to Defenses</strong> and <strong>Divert Power to Weapons</strong> tactics:</p>","lid":"ms_9b86g4zViEzAQAGlFHrmT","integrated":[],"license":"","license_level":1,"name":"Power Distribution Systems","source":null,"tags":[{"val":1,"tag":{"id":"060yGC97tWUriLGk","fallback_lid":"tg_unique","type":"tag","reg_name":"comp_core"}}],"sp":1,"uses":0,"actions":[{"lid":"act_A29IKTo_IEGVwvUWWBTGU","name":"Divert Power to Defenses (Tactic)","activation":"Quick","terse":"Terse Description","detail":"<h1>Reloading 2</h1>\n<p>Add <strong>1 Charge Counter</strong> to a <strong>CHARGE</strong> weapon in your battlegroup. The ship equipped with that weapon gains <strong>+2 Defense</strong> and your battlegroup gains <strong>+1d6 Interdiction</strong> until the end of your next turn.</p>","cost":1,"frequency":"","init":"","trigger":"","pilot":true,"mech":true,"heat_cost":0,"synergy_locations":[],"damage":[],"range":[],"confirm":["CONFIRM"],"hide_active":false,"ignore_used":false,"log":""},{"lid":"act_e5fK7X28ZoRjDeLUMcWCV","name":"Divert Power to Weapons (Tactic)","activation":"Quick","terse":"Terse Description","detail":"<h1>Limited 1</h1>\n<p>You shunt power from a ship&rsquo;s defenses straight into weapon systems. Remove <strong>1 Charge Counter</strong> from a <strong>CHARGE</strong> weapon in your battlegroup, but all attacks against the ship equipped with that weapon gain <strong>+1 ACCURACY</strong> and damage reduction from <strong>Interdiction</strong> applied to that ship is only half as effective (requiring <strong>2 Interdiction</strong> to prevent <strong>1 damage</strong>) until the end of your next turn.</p>","cost":1,"frequency":"","init":"","trigger":"","pilot":true,"mech":true,"heat_cost":0,"synergy_locations":[],"damage":[],"range":[],"confirm":["CONFIRM"],"hide_active":false,"ignore_used":false,"log":""}],"bonuses":[],"synergies":[],"description":"<p>Advanced PD systems are managed by officers working in concert with a legion partition to distribute power across an active ship far more efficiently than purely automated systems. The benefits allow for greater moment-to-moment prioritization of ship power as needed, whether for offensive or defensive purposes.</p>","type":"System"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"HHrm6UaHtCrg3Wzn":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"HlKRITUw8cUmCyLR","name":"Impossible Dodge","type":"mech_system","img":"systems/lancer/assets/icons/mech_system.svg","data":{"cascading":false,"counters":[{"lid":"tempLID","name":"Reloading","val":0,"max":3,"min":0}],"deployables":[],"destroyed":false,"effect":"<p>During the <strong>Logistics Phase</strong>, you may choose one of your ships. The use of sudden counterfactual positioning &ldquo;removes that ship from play&rdquo; until the end of your next turn. While removed from play it:<br /><br />&bull; can&rsquo;t be targeted by attacks and effects or take damage <br />&bull; can&rsquo;t use any weapons, upgrades, or traits <br />&bull; doesn&rsquo;t provide any other benefits to your battlegroup, including <strong>INTERDICTION</strong> bonuses <br />&bull; automatically evades all active <strong>PAYLOAD</strong> attacks that reach 0 <strong>Flight Counters</strong> during the same <strong>Logistics Phase</strong> as this system was used.<br /><br /><strong>AREA-TARGET PAYLOAD</strong> attacks deal damage to the other ships in the battlegroup as normal.</p>","lid":"ms_NPMzsJNlr6yzrz9D1Lah9","integrated":[],"license":"","license_level":1,"name":"Impossible Dodge","source":null,"tags":[{"val":1,"tag":{"id":"060yGC97tWUriLGk","fallback_lid":"tg_unique","type":"tag","reg_name":"comp_core"}},{"val":1,"tag":{"id":"y26LL8HRL2XMZuxM","fallback_lid":"tg_78SWgJLYkLyBOoZqDfDxY","type":"tag","reg_name":"game"}},{"val":"3","tag":{"id":"4zljqurutuldbJiO","fallback_lid":"tg_8FBdSdkbLqsDsDmyJwlCa","type":"tag","reg_name":"game"}}],"sp":1,"uses":0,"actions":[],"bonuses":[],"synergies":[],"description":"<p>No ship can move like that!</p>","type":"System"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"HHrm6UaHtCrg3Wzn":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"M7xDQGtN8gF8h9gK","name":"Anti-Cognition Hyperfractal","type":"mech_system","img":"systems/lancer/assets/icons/mech_system.svg","data":{"cascading":false,"counters":[],"deployables":[],"destroyed":false,"effect":"<p>During the <strong>Logistics Phase</strong>, you may add <strong>1 Flight Counter</strong> to up to two active hostile <strong>PAYLOAD</strong> attacks. A hostile battlegroup with <strong>PAYLOAD</strong> attacks affected by this may ignore it by taking <strong>3 AREA-TARGET</strong> damage per <strong>Flight Counter</strong> negated. This damage cannot be interdicted. If the effect on one or both <strong>PAYLOAD</strong> attacks is ignored, immediately remove <strong>1 Refresh Counter</strong> from this system.</p>","lid":"ms_PIFa2VLRUXPZujn2nEClo","integrated":[],"license":"","license_level":2,"name":"Anti-Cognition Hyperfractal","source":null,"tags":[{"val":1,"tag":{"id":"060yGC97tWUriLGk","fallback_lid":"tg_unique","type":"tag","reg_name":"comp_core"}},{"val":1,"tag":{"id":"y26LL8HRL2XMZuxM","fallback_lid":"tg_78SWgJLYkLyBOoZqDfDxY","type":"tag","reg_name":"game"}},{"val":"3","tag":{"id":"4zljqurutuldbJiO","fallback_lid":"tg_8FBdSdkbLqsDsDmyJwlCa","type":"tag","reg_name":"game"}}],"sp":1,"uses":0,"actions":[],"bonuses":[],"synergies":[],"description":"<p>Your fleet legion pierces the enemy legion&rsquo;s manifold ego barriers, implanting a germ of anticognitive thought. It blooms and grows endlessly, disrupting simul- neural pathways and creating excited hyperfractal redundancy loops. With the right effort, the enemy gestalt will begin to fragment and cascade &ndash; just as planned.</p>","type":"System"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"HHrm6UaHtCrg3Wzn":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"PXFy2IYAlFe9LZFT","name":"Bulwark Redundancies","type":"mech_system","img":"systems/lancer/assets/icons/mech_system.svg","data":{"cascading":false,"counters":[],"deployables":[],"destroyed":false,"effect":"<p>This ship gains +3 HP. This system can only be taken once per ship</p>","lid":"eaa55282-80c2-429f-9578-713666632d6e","integrated":[],"license":"","license_level":1,"name":"Bulwark Redundancies","source":null,"tags":[],"sp":1,"uses":0,"actions":[],"bonuses":[{"lid":"hp","val":"3","damage_types":{"Burn":true,"Energy":true,"Explosive":true,"Heat":true,"Kinetic":true,"Variable":true},"range_types":{"Blast":true,"Burst":true,"Cone":true,"Line":true,"Range":true,"Thrown":true,"Threat":true},"weapon_types":{"CQB":true,"Cannon":true,"Launcher":true,"Melee":true,"Nexus":true,"Rifle":true},"weapon_sizes":{"Auxiliary":true,"Heavy":true,"Main":true,"Superheavy":true},"overwrite":false,"replace":false}],"synergies":[],"description":"<p>Extensive superstructural modifications and endo/exo uparmoring can help a ship survive hits that would otherwise kill a stock version of the same vessel.</p>","type":"System"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"HHrm6UaHtCrg3Wzn":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.mech_system.Wblf2FaQlhgFIPa1"}}}
{"_id":"PXypdbpjUFBlLCnj","name":"Aurora Stealth Shrouding","type":"mech_system","img":"systems/lancer/assets/icons/mech_system.svg","data":{"cascading":false,"counters":[{"lid":"tempLID","name":"Whiteout Limited","val":1,"max":1,"min":0},{"lid":"tempLID","name":"Thermal Spoofing Limited","val":2,"max":2,"min":0},{"lid":"tempLID","name":"Thermal Spoofing Reload","val":0,"max":2,"min":0}],"deployables":[],"destroyed":false,"effect":"<p>Whenever your battlegroup moves or is moved two or more range bands during a round, you immediately become <strong>BOLSTERED</strong> until the start of the next <strong>Action Phase</strong>. If you are already <strong>BOLSTERED</strong>, you may clear <strong>LOCK ON</strong> from a <strong>CAPITAL SHIP </strong>in your battlegroup instead. Additionally, gain the <strong>Whiteout</strong> maneuver and <strong>Thermal Spoofing</strong> tactic.</p>","lid":"ms_4PJ1qXGzRZoh31IvWD3_D","integrated":[],"license":"","license_level":3,"name":"Aurora Stealth Shrouding","source":null,"tags":[{"val":1,"tag":{"id":"060yGC97tWUriLGk","fallback_lid":"tg_unique","type":"tag","reg_name":"comp_core"}}],"sp":1,"uses":0,"actions":[{"lid":"act_Dr5PSAB9UbqThspwpLtYs","name":"Whiteout (Maneuver)","activation":"Full","terse":"Terse Description","detail":"<h1>Limited 1</h1>\n<p>Your battlegroup may fall back or advance one range band and is then obscured by a massive flare of thermal energy that blinds enemy sensors. While obscured, your battlegroup and its ships:<br /><br />&bull; can&rsquo;t be targeted by attacks and effects or take damage <br />&bull; can&rsquo;t use any weapons, upgrades, or traits <br />&bull; don&rsquo;t provide any other benefits<br /><br />Your battlegroup continues to add and remove counters during the <strong>Logistics Phase</strong> as normal. Payload attacks targeting your battlegroup or ships during this time cannot go below <strong>1 Flight Counter</strong> by any means.<br /><br />Your battlegroup reappears during the next <strong>Impact Phase</strong> after all other battlegroups have chosen targets and rolled to hit. You may then choose targets and roll to hit with any ready <strong>CHARGE</strong> weapons. The damage from your <strong>CHARGE</strong> weapons is applied before any other damage is rolled. If this is enough to destroy a hostile ship, it is destroyed before it can fire its own <strong>CHARGE</strong> weapons and its damage and any other effects are negated. The ship equipped with this upgrade then takes <strong>1d6 damage</strong> from thermal overload that ignores <strong>OVERSHIELD</strong> and cannot be prevented in any way.</p>","cost":1,"frequency":"","init":"","trigger":"","pilot":true,"mech":true,"heat_cost":0,"synergy_locations":[],"damage":[],"range":[],"confirm":["CONFIRM"],"hide_active":false,"ignore_used":false,"log":""},{"lid":"act_J4ZghkxSfQCXjVrSMrVPj","name":"Thermal Spoofing (Tactic)","activation":"Quick","terse":"Terse Description","detail":"<h1>Limited 2, Reloading 2</h1>\n<p>Choose up to two of the following effects:<br /><br />&bull; Clear <strong>LOCK ON</strong> from a<strong> CAPITAL SHIP</strong> in your battlegroup or from an allied <strong>CAPITAL SHIP </strong>in the same range band. <br />&bull; Add <strong>1 Flight Counter</strong> to an active <strong>PAYLOAD</strong> attack targeting your battlegroup or any of your ships. <br />&bull; All single-target attacks against a single <strong>CAPITAL SHIP</strong> in your battlegroup receive <strong>+1 DIFFICULTY</strong> until the end of your next turn.</p>","cost":1,"frequency":"","init":"","trigger":"","pilot":true,"mech":true,"heat_cost":0,"synergy_locations":[],"damage":[],"range":[],"confirm":["CONFIRM"],"hide_active":false,"ignore_used":false,"log":""}],"bonuses":[],"synergies":[],"description":"<p>&ldquo;Stealth&rdquo; in a naval context is largely a matter of inverse thermal concealment; combat-ready ships simply cannot hope to conceal their heat signatures from enemy detection, and attempting to minimize heat emissions through internal sink storage results in crews being cooked alive. As such, effective concealment involves the emission of thermal plumes via ejected waste heat mediums or the unfurling of enormous spools of conductive nanocarbon filaments to act as radiator arrays. This massive heat output prevents enemy sensors from maintaining positive-target identification and allows shrouded vessels to effectively maneuver while masking their true positions.</p>","type":"System"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"HHrm6UaHtCrg3Wzn":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"Q4angNylLHdN5EXr","name":"Piper Drones","type":"mech_system","img":"systems/lancer/assets/icons/mech_system.svg","data":{"cascading":false,"counters":[],"deployables":[],"destroyed":false,"effect":"<p>During the <strong>Logistics Phase</strong>, you may choose one:<br /><br />&bull; Add<strong> 1</strong> <strong>Flight Counter</strong> to an active hostile <strong>PAYLOAD</strong> attack targeting one of your ships or your battlegroup. <br />&bull; Redirect an active hostile <strong>PAYLOAD</strong> attack toward one of your ships or your battlegroup.</p>","lid":"ms_0FlGlWTHk9IGgfXWq7Wyz","integrated":[],"license":"","license_level":0,"name":"Piper Drones","source":null,"tags":[{"val":1,"tag":{"id":"GsPrdH4DG2a0xrTW","fallback_lid":"tg_limited","type":"tag","reg_name":"comp_core"}},{"val":1,"tag":{"id":"060yGC97tWUriLGk","fallback_lid":"tg_unique","type":"tag","reg_name":"comp_core"}}],"sp":1,"uses":0,"actions":[],"bonuses":[],"synergies":[],"description":"<p>Piper drones are defensive, single-use drones fired from ships under threat from guided missiles. Once launched, piper drones emit like-signatures cloned from their parent ship, diverting incoming missiles via signal spoofing.</p>","type":"System"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"HHrm6UaHtCrg3Wzn":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"SFsHZOFo45ewTyYC","name":"Veteran Crews","type":"mech_system","img":"systems/lancer/assets/icons/mech_system.svg","data":{"cascading":false,"counters":[],"deployables":[],"destroyed":false,"effect":"<p>You may reroll one of your attack rolls but must keep the second result. On a reroll result of 20+, you do not expend this system&rsquo;s <strong>Limited</strong> use.</p>","lid":"ms_frbZrzfhHJXzLAvgxOEv0","integrated":[],"license":"","license_level":0,"name":"Veteran Crews","source":null,"tags":[{"val":1,"tag":{"id":"GsPrdH4DG2a0xrTW","fallback_lid":"tg_limited","type":"tag","reg_name":"comp_core"}}],"sp":1,"uses":0,"actions":[],"bonuses":[],"synergies":[],"description":"<p>Veteran crews have been through the tense dance of interstellar combat before and are well prepared to handle the stress and chaos each new engagement brings.</p>","type":"System"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"HHrm6UaHtCrg3Wzn":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"SoHFuUM38N1tLljZ","name":"Battlespace CIC","type":"mech_system","img":"systems/lancer/assets/icons/mech_system.svg","data":{"cascading":false,"counters":[{"lid":"tempLID","name":"Adjust Bearing Reload","val":0,"max":2,"min":0},{"lid":"tempLID","name":"Coordinated Impact Limited","val":2,"max":2,"min":0},{"lid":"tempLID","name":"Coordinated Impact Reload","val":0,"max":2,"min":0}],"deployables":[],"destroyed":false,"effect":"<p>When you assign <strong>FRIGATES</strong> to a <strong>Defensive Screen</strong>, you may assign them to allied battlegroups in the range band either directly ahead of you or directly behind you. Additionally, gain the <strong>Adjust Bearing</strong> maneuver and <strong>Coordinated Impact</strong> tactic:</p>","lid":"ms_5EbscahrKBZWlxMSOKagr","integrated":[],"license":"","license_level":3,"name":"Battlespace CIC","source":null,"tags":[],"sp":1,"uses":0,"actions":[{"lid":"act_8yoEO7DXqsIpQMOkPnnyq","name":"Adjust Bearing (Maneuver)","activation":"Full","terse":"Terse Description","detail":"<h1>Reloading 2</h1>\n<p>Your battlegroup may fall back or advance one range band, and you may move an allied battlegroup back or forward one range band. If you use this maneuver at <strong>Range 5-3</strong>, you may also <strong>LOCK ON</strong> to a hostile <strong>CAPITAL SHIP</strong> or <strong>ESCORT</strong>.</p>","cost":1,"frequency":"","init":"","trigger":"","pilot":true,"mech":true,"heat_cost":0,"synergy_locations":[],"damage":[],"range":[],"confirm":["CONFIRM"],"hide_active":false,"ignore_used":false,"log":""},{"lid":"act_KOiPQaIDjd6svzdSEjdic","name":"Coordinated Impact (Tactic)","activation":"Quick","terse":"Terse Description","detail":"<h1>Limited 2, Reloading 2</h1>\n<p>Choose one:<br /><br />&bull; Add or remove <strong>1 Flight Counter</strong> from up to two of your active <strong>PAYLOAD</strong> attacks or those belonging to allied battlegroups. <br />&bull; Choose two weapons belonging to you or allied battlegroups and extend their maximum and minimum ranges by 1 for their next attack (for example, a weapon with <strong>Range 4-2</strong> would have <strong>Range 5-1</strong>). This effect does not stack.</p>","cost":1,"frequency":"","init":"","trigger":"","pilot":true,"mech":true,"heat_cost":0,"synergy_locations":[],"damage":[],"range":[],"confirm":["CONFIRM"],"hide_active":false,"ignore_used":false,"log":""}],"bonuses":[],"synergies":[],"description":"<p>Developed as a joint venture between Harrison Armory&rsquo;s Think Tank and Smith-Shimano&rsquo;s Ontologics &amp; Cosubjectvity Research Campus, Battlespace is a next-generation command information center architecture that allows for more efficient and agile information flow between fleet legions and human bridge elements. Though complete 1&ndash;1 human/legion cosubjectivity remains an as yet elusive goal, this development represents a significant step forward in full-spectrum fleet command capability</p>","type":"System"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"HHrm6UaHtCrg3Wzn":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"TQomVgc2ggliWQXW","name":"Subjective Syzygy","type":"mech_system","img":"systems/lancer/assets/icons/mech_system.svg","data":{"cascading":false,"counters":[{"lid":"tempLID","name":"Reloading","val":0,"max":3,"min":0}],"deployables":[],"destroyed":false,"effect":"<p>When a hostile ship makes a single-target attack roll against a ship in your battlegroup or an allied ship in your range band, you may force them to reroll the attack and take the worst result.</p>","lid":"ms_qpTCMfpGOYJ_6YVMQtL-k","integrated":[],"license":"","license_level":1,"name":"Subjective Syzygy","source":null,"tags":[{"val":1,"tag":{"id":"060yGC97tWUriLGk","fallback_lid":"tg_unique","type":"tag","reg_name":"comp_core"}},{"val":1,"tag":{"id":"y26LL8HRL2XMZuxM","fallback_lid":"tg_78SWgJLYkLyBOoZqDfDxY","type":"tag","reg_name":"game"}},{"val":"3","tag":{"id":"4zljqurutuldbJiO","fallback_lid":"tg_8FBdSdkbLqsDsDmyJwlCa","type":"tag","reg_name":"game"}}],"sp":1,"uses":0,"actions":[],"bonuses":[],"synergies":[],"description":"<p>A subjective syzygy is a crude but effective legionspace attack, smashing through ontological defenses like a hammer and sending enemy legions recoiling from the assault against their very sense of self. In layman&rsquo;s terms, the syzygy momentarily forces a target gestalt to be overlaid by and aligned with an attacker&rsquo;s own systems-bolstered legionspace, blanking out the target&rsquo;s legion for brief but precious seconds.</p>","type":"System"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"HHrm6UaHtCrg3Wzn":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"XEmX9sqUdoQJLv9J","name":"Subline Berth","type":"mech_system","img":"systems/lancer/assets/icons/mech_system.svg","data":{"cascading":false,"counters":[],"deployables":[],"destroyed":false,"effect":"<p>This ship gains <strong>+1 ESCORT</strong> slot.</p>","lid":"ms_92zOxr_et_pLKspecEhQr","integrated":[],"license":"","license_level":0,"name":"Subline Berth","source":null,"tags":[{"val":1,"tag":{"id":"060yGC97tWUriLGk","fallback_lid":"tg_unique","type":"tag","reg_name":"comp_core"}}],"sp":1,"uses":0,"actions":[],"bonuses":[],"synergies":[],"description":"<p>The primary limiting factor in deploying subline vessels is one of logistics. These ships frequently sacrifice all but the bare essentials in order to maximize their effective firepower, restricting their maximum deployment range and limiting the time they can remain combat effective without resupply. These restrictions can be overcome through the incorporation of additional supply holds, hull upgrades, and logistical infrastructure, allowing any ship of the line to manage and maintain their own escorts for extended durations.</p>","type":"System"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"HHrm6UaHtCrg3Wzn":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"bpa9n9JhSAqON22w","name":"Predict/Overlay Shield Projector","type":"mech_system","img":"systems/lancer/assets/icons/mech_system.svg","data":{"cascading":false,"counters":[],"deployables":[],"destroyed":false,"effect":"<p>During the <strong>Impact Phase</strong>, you may reduce incoming damage assigned to a <strong>CAPITAL SHIP</strong> in your battlegroup from a <strong>SUPERHEAVY</strong> weapon by <strong>6</strong>. At <strong>Range 5</strong>, this damage reduction is increased to <strong>10</strong> instead.</p>","lid":"ms_U9DcAXwDqInTg3UTcV2hx","integrated":[],"license":"","license_level":0,"name":"Predict/Overlay Shield Projector","source":null,"tags":[{"val":1,"tag":{"id":"060yGC97tWUriLGk","fallback_lid":"tg_unique","type":"tag","reg_name":"comp_core"}},{"val":1,"tag":{"id":"GsPrdH4DG2a0xrTW","fallback_lid":"tg_limited","type":"tag","reg_name":"comp_core"}}],"sp":1,"uses":0,"actions":[],"bonuses":[],"synergies":[],"description":"<p>P/OS projectors flash-layer alternating fields of magnetics, kinetics, coherent particles, and shimmering waveform shields over friendly ships under threat. These layered systems, flashed for a moment, can precisely dismantle, deflect, and defray incoming fire against critical targets, turning what might otherwise have been a kill shot into something more survivable, if only just.</p>","type":"System"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"HHrm6UaHtCrg3Wzn":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"dYwaNqYGk8UINkn7","name":"Flagship","type":"mech_system","img":"systems/lancer/assets/icons/mech_system.svg","data":{"cascading":false,"counters":[],"deployables":[],"destroyed":false,"effect":"<p>+3 HP, +1d6 Interdiction, +1 System slot</p>","lid":"0ef71c6b-6e97-4616-88c4-6ad84bb9765a","integrated":[],"license":"","license_level":0,"name":"Flagship","source":null,"tags":[{"tag":{"id":"060yGC97tWUriLGk","fallback_lid":"tg_unique","type":"tag","reg_name":"comp_core"}}],"sp":0,"uses":0,"actions":[],"bonuses":[{"lid":"hp","val":"3","damage_types":{"Burn":true,"Energy":true,"Explosive":true,"Heat":true,"Kinetic":true,"Variable":true},"range_types":{"Blast":true,"Burst":true,"Cone":true,"Line":true,"Range":true,"Thrown":true,"Threat":true},"weapon_types":{"CQB":true,"Cannon":true,"Launcher":true,"Melee":true,"Nexus":true,"Rifle":true},"weapon_sizes":{"Auxiliary":true,"Heavy":true,"Main":true,"Superheavy":true},"overwrite":false,"replace":false},{"lid":"sp","val":"1","damage_types":{"Burn":true,"Energy":true,"Explosive":true,"Heat":true,"Kinetic":true,"Variable":true},"range_types":{"Blast":true,"Burst":true,"Cone":true,"Line":true,"Range":true,"Thrown":true,"Threat":true},"weapon_types":{"CQB":true,"Cannon":true,"Launcher":true,"Melee":true,"Nexus":true,"Rifle":true},"weapon_sizes":{"Auxiliary":true,"Heavy":true,"Main":true,"Superheavy":true},"overwrite":false,"replace":false}],"synergies":[],"description":"<p> This is the vessel from which your character will command their battlegroup and the one that will – should it be destroyed – result in the death of your character (unless they make it to an escape pod). Your FLAGSHIP gains +3 HP, +1d6 INTERDICTION, and +1 SYSTEM slot. These bonuses represent the customizations that have gone into making this your command vessel. Any type of CAPITAL SHIP can serve as a FLAGSHIP; while battleships are the most popular choice, many commanders prefer to oversee matters from the bridge of a frigate or carrier. Note that losing your FLAGSHIP during an engagement does not prevent you from continuing to fight on with the remainder of your forces.</p>","type":"System"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"HHrm6UaHtCrg3Wzn":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.mech_system.mHVTFyEDsR5InFcc"}}}
{"_id":"h2FyyDyI2DEqumnA","name":"Steady... Now!","type":"mech_system","img":"systems/lancer/assets/icons/mech_system.svg","data":{"cascading":false,"counters":[],"deployables":[],"destroyed":false,"effect":"<p>Gain the <strong>Steady&hellip; Now!</strong> tactic:</p>","lid":"ms_C7CfAjXo3tVZxNA6dgYkQ","integrated":[],"license":"","license_level":0,"name":"Steady... Now!","source":null,"tags":[{"val":1,"tag":{"id":"060yGC97tWUriLGk","fallback_lid":"tg_unique","type":"tag","reg_name":"comp_core"}},{"val":1,"tag":{"id":"GsPrdH4DG2a0xrTW","fallback_lid":"tg_limited","type":"tag","reg_name":"comp_core"}}],"sp":1,"uses":0,"actions":[{"lid":"act_5YiMmCvD12nhStPpP7CuJ","name":"Steady... Now! (Tactic)","activation":"Quick","terse":"<p>Choose a weapon in your battlegroup with the <strong>CHARGE</strong> tag. Your next attack with that weapon gains <strong>+1 ACCURACY</strong> and <strong>+X RELIABLE</strong>, where X is based on your range band (i.e., <strong>Extreme Range</strong> grants <strong>+5</strong>, <strong>Long Range</strong> grants <strong>+4</strong>, etc).</p>","detail":"<p>Choose a weapon in your battlegroup with the <strong>CHARGE</strong> tag. Your next attack with that weapon gains <strong>+1 ACCURACY</strong> and <strong>+X RELIABLE</strong>, where X is based on your range band (i.e., <strong>Extreme Range</strong> grants <strong>+5</strong>, <strong>Long Range</strong> grants <strong>+4</strong>, etc).</p>","cost":1,"frequency":"","init":"","trigger":"","pilot":true,"mech":true,"heat_cost":0,"synergy_locations":[],"damage":[],"range":[],"confirm":["CONFIRM"],"hide_active":false,"ignore_used":false,"log":""}],"bonuses":[],"synergies":[],"description":"<p>The key is balance: never fire too early, and always before it is too late.</p>","type":"System"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"HHrm6UaHtCrg3Wzn":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"i5odj1HASzyhap6h","name":"Single-Plane Shield","type":"mech_system","img":"systems/lancer/assets/icons/mech_system.svg","data":{"cascading":false,"counters":[],"deployables":[],"destroyed":false,"effect":"<p>During the <strong>Impact Phase</strong>, you may reroll your <strong>Interdiction</strong> roll and take the best result.</p>","lid":"ms_I98skGflu19_LJ63SU_rU","integrated":[],"license":"","license_level":0,"name":"Single-Plane Shield","source":null,"tags":[{"val":1,"tag":{"id":"GsPrdH4DG2a0xrTW","fallback_lid":"tg_limited","type":"tag","reg_name":"comp_core"}}],"sp":1,"uses":0,"actions":[],"bonuses":[],"synergies":[],"description":"<p>Many ships of the line use strong-energy systems to supplement fleetwide point defenses. More effective against slower forms of ordnance than against high- velocity and directed-energy munitions, these shields nonetheless serve as excellent additional protection against massed salvos of missiles or torpedoes.</p>","type":"System"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"HHrm6UaHtCrg3Wzn":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"iEhR4ebSyYo5E3o8","name":"Insightful Commanders","type":"mech_system","img":"systems/lancer/assets/icons/mech_system.svg","data":{"cascading":false,"counters":[],"deployables":[],"destroyed":false,"effect":"<p>1/round, when a hostile effect or ability forces you to move back or forward any number of range bands, your next single-target attack gains <strong>+1 ACCURACY,</strong> or <strong>+2 ACCURACY </strong>if you are attacking from <strong>Range 5-4</strong>. This effect lasts until the end of your next turn and does not stack.<br /><br />Additionally, 1/engagement when moved by a hostile effect or ability, you may instead attack with a single <strong>PRIMARY</strong> weapon of your choice before or after the hostile movement.</p>","lid":"ms_0XkKWxKvdc9ejnDIWiFPD","integrated":[],"license":"","license_level":0,"name":"Insightful Commanders","source":null,"tags":[],"sp":1,"uses":0,"actions":[],"bonuses":[],"synergies":[],"description":"<p>Through hard-won experience, advanced predictive modeling, or simply a keen sense of tactical intuition, your battlegroup&rsquo;s commanders are adept at reading the shifting tides of battle and responding accordingly.</p>","type":"System"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"HHrm6UaHtCrg3Wzn":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"p9qLLN8KVtBapUo5","name":"Aggressive Commanders","type":"mech_system","img":"systems/lancer/assets/icons/mech_system.svg","data":{"cascading":false,"counters":[{"lid":"tempLID","name":"1/Engagement","val":1,"max":1,"min":0}],"deployables":[],"destroyed":false,"effect":"<p>All single-target attacks made by and against you at <strong>Range 2-0</strong> gain <strong>+1 ACCURACY</strong>. Additionally, 1/ engagement, you may choose one:<br /><br />&bull; When a hostile effect or ability forces your battlegroup to move forward any number of range bands, one of your <strong>CAPITAL SHIPS</strong> gains <strong>5 OVERSHIELD</strong>.</p>\n<p>&bull; When a hostile effect or ability forces an allied battlegroup to move forward any number of range bands, your battlegroup moves instead. If this prevents a hostile ship from targeting the allied battlegroup with an attack or ability as part of that same action, it may target you instead.</p>","lid":"ms_svLLxLzyvLw_2T2Q_5LDd","integrated":[],"license":"","license_level":0,"name":"Aggressive Commanders","source":null,"tags":[],"sp":1,"uses":0,"actions":[],"bonuses":[],"synergies":[],"description":"<p>Your battlegroup&rsquo;s combat doctrine emphasizes aggressive movement, closing gaps and plotting courses that more timid commanders would eschew. This impetus is not without sacrifice, often requiring defensive positioning and predictability to be traded for a chance to take the fight directly to your enemies.</p>","type":"System"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"HHrm6UaHtCrg3Wzn":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"q2pD4VDUJahsFhFI","name":"Fighter-Launch Catapults","type":"mech_system","img":"systems/lancer/assets/icons/mech_system.svg","data":{"cascading":false,"counters":[],"deployables":[],"destroyed":false,"effect":"<p>This ship gains <strong>+1 WING</strong> slot.</p>","lid":"ms_fCuixrNjY7iZkV_b8fZdf","integrated":[],"license":"","license_level":0,"name":"Fighter-Launch Catapults","source":null,"tags":[{"val":1,"tag":{"id":"060yGC97tWUriLGk","fallback_lid":"tg_unique","type":"tag","reg_name":"comp_core"}}],"sp":1,"uses":0,"actions":[],"bonuses":[],"synergies":[],"description":"<p>While dedicated carriers have an uncontested place in conventional naval doctrine, many commanders value the versatility of carrier tactics enough to modify other ships modified so they can maintain and launch a modest complement of fighter-tier strike craft or mounted chassis. This can involve either internal retrofitting or the addition of externally mounted hangar bays affixed to a ship&rsquo;s hull.</p>","type":"System"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"HHrm6UaHtCrg3Wzn":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"qwDA37uvpSY5KfUo","name":"Fire for Effect","type":"mech_system","img":"systems/lancer/assets/icons/mech_system.svg","data":{"cascading":false,"counters":[],"deployables":[],"destroyed":false,"effect":"<p>Gain the <strong>Fire for Effect</strong> tactic:</p>","lid":"ms_u3PrHYNK9cE3NazO5KWOQ","integrated":[],"license":"","license_level":0,"name":"Fire for Effect","source":null,"tags":[{"val":1,"tag":{"id":"060yGC97tWUriLGk","fallback_lid":"tg_unique","type":"tag","reg_name":"comp_core"}},{"val":1,"tag":{"id":"GsPrdH4DG2a0xrTW","fallback_lid":"tg_limited","type":"tag","reg_name":"comp_core"}}],"sp":1,"uses":0,"actions":[{"lid":"act_s7b8BPkEfpEAaJlPzjNQ3","name":"Fire for Effect (Tactic)","activation":"Quick","terse":"<p>Nominate a hostile battlegroup as a priority target. Until the start of the next Logistics Phase, all single-target attacks made against that battlegroup gain +1 ACCURACY.</p>","detail":"<p>Nominate a hostile battlegroup as a priority target. Until the start of the next Logistics Phase, all single-target attacks made against that battlegroup gain +1 ACCURACY.</p>","cost":1,"frequency":"","init":"","trigger":"","pilot":true,"mech":true,"heat_cost":0,"synergy_locations":[],"damage":[],"range":[],"confirm":["CONFIRM"],"hide_active":false,"ignore_used":false,"log":""}],"bonuses":[],"synergies":[],"description":"<p>Bracketing is satisfactory and trajectories are true: all guns, fire for effect.</p>","type":"System"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"HHrm6UaHtCrg3Wzn":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"rM2eaPcVZgu5IhIF","name":"\"Sandstorm\" Vanguard","type":"mech_system","img":"systems/lancer/assets/icons/mech_system.svg","data":{"cascading":false,"counters":[{"lid":"tempLID","name":"Slingshot Limited","val":1,"max":1,"min":0},{"lid":"tempLID","name":"Lithoscreen Limited","val":2,"max":2,"min":0},{"lid":"tempLID","name":"Lithoscreen Reload","val":0,"max":2,"min":0}],"deployables":[],"destroyed":false,"effect":"<p>Your battlegroup gains <strong>+2 INTERDICTION</strong>, and the <strong>Slingshot</strong> maneuver and <strong>Lithoscreen</strong> tactic:</p>","lid":"ms_6HsO2swMHd84uAjmJYck9","integrated":[],"license":"","license_level":3,"name":"\"Sandstorm\" Vanguard","source":null,"tags":[],"sp":1,"uses":0,"actions":[{"lid":"act_dL-8WdTRurHw8ga8qC0cj","name":"Slingshot (Maneuver)","activation":"Full","terse":"Terse Description","detail":"<h1>Limited 1</h1>\n<p>Your battlegroup may advance one range band forward, after which you lob a group of asteroids at a hostile <strong>CAPITAL SHIP</strong>. This counts as an attack using the following profile:<br /><br /><strong>SUPERHEAVY, SINGLE/AREA-TARGET, PAYLOAD</strong><br /><br /><strong>Range 3&ndash;0, 10 single-target damage + 4 area- target damage</strong><br /><br /><strong>Interdiction</strong> against this attack is applied to its <strong>AREA-TARGET</strong> damage first. This attack ignores hostile effects and abilities that add or remove <strong>Flight Counters</strong> or destroy <strong>Payload</strong> attacks.<br /><br />On hit, this attack erupts into a dangerous cloud of debris that lasts until the start of the next <strong>Logistics Phase</strong>. For this duration, the next time the target battlegroup would use an ability or effect that forces you or an allied battlegroup to move, it takes <strong>2d6 AREA-TARGET</strong> damage and all of its single-target attack rolls receive <strong>+1 DIFFICULTY</strong> until the end of its next turn.</p>","cost":1,"frequency":"","init":"","trigger":"","pilot":true,"mech":true,"heat_cost":0,"synergy_locations":[],"damage":[],"range":[],"confirm":["CONFIRM"],"hide_active":false,"ignore_used":false,"log":""},{"lid":"act_CdTXkO2qK2KdfWCqGfVyw","name":"Lithoscreen (Tactic)","activation":"Quick","terse":"Terse Description","detail":"<h1>Limited 2, Reloading 2</h1>\n<p>One<strong> Capital Ship</strong> in your battlegroup gains <strong>5 OVERSHIELD</strong>. The next time a hostile <strong>CAPITAL SHIP</strong>, <strong>ESCORT</strong>, or <strong>WING</strong> reduces this <strong>OVERSHIELD</strong> to 0 during the <strong>Action Phase</strong>, the attacker takes 3 damage.</p>","cost":1,"frequency":"","init":"","trigger":"","pilot":true,"mech":true,"heat_cost":0,"synergy_locations":[],"damage":[],"range":[],"confirm":["CONFIRM"],"hide_active":false,"ignore_used":false,"log":""}],"bonuses":[],"synergies":[],"description":"No description","type":"System"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"HHrm6UaHtCrg3Wzn":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"sFp1kgZG7c2e3A82","name":"Brace for Impact","type":"mech_system","img":"systems/lancer/assets/icons/mech_system.svg","data":{"cascading":false,"counters":[],"deployables":[],"destroyed":false,"effect":"<p>Choose one when you use this system:<br /><br />&bull; You may activate this system during the <strong>Impact Phase</strong> after attacks have been rolled and damage has been assigned: all damage taken by ships in your battlegroup is reduced by half until the end of your next turn. You may not use any tactics or perform any maneuvers during your next turn except for <strong>All Ahead Full</strong> or <strong>Retrograde Burn</strong>.</p>\n<p>&bull; You may use the <strong>Brace for Impact</strong> tactic below during your turn.</p>","lid":"ms_-9eVVod3Ni3x5PY6sVOfg","integrated":[],"license":"","license_level":0,"name":"Brace for Impact","source":null,"tags":[{"val":1,"tag":{"id":"GsPrdH4DG2a0xrTW","fallback_lid":"tg_limited","type":"tag","reg_name":"comp_core"}}],"sp":1,"uses":0,"actions":[{"lid":"act_IcfjKiV9TCzTzF2l--L2g","name":"Brace for Impact (Tactic)","activation":"Quick","terse":"<p>Your battlegroup becomes BOLSTERED until the end of your next turn.</p>","detail":"<p>Your battlegroup becomes BOLSTERED until the end of your next turn.</p>","cost":1,"frequency":"","init":"","trigger":"","pilot":true,"mech":true,"heat_cost":0,"synergy_locations":[],"damage":[],"range":[],"confirm":["CONFIRM"],"hide_active":false,"ignore_used":false,"log":""}],"bonuses":[],"synergies":[],"description":"<p>The order that every commander dreads to give.</p>","type":"System"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"HHrm6UaHtCrg3Wzn":3},"flags":{}}
